This repository uses a generic, tool-agnostic AI instruction system.

Canonical instructions live under:

- AGENTS.md
- .ai/README.md
- .ai/skills/
- .ai/roles/
- .ai/workflows/

Do not duplicate skills, roles, or workflows under .cursor/. This file is a thin
adapter that points to `.ai/` — the single source of truth.

Before editing code, read the relevant `.ai/` skill. Always read
`.ai/skills/project-architecture.md` first; if a task spans multiple areas, read
all relevant skills before editing.

For Python implementation:
- .ai/skills/senior-python-engineering.md

For tests:
- .ai/skills/testing.md

For architecture changes:
- .ai/skills/architecture-review.md

For code review:
- .ai/skills/code-review.md

For refactoring:
- .ai/skills/refactoring.md

For documentation:
- .ai/skills/documentation.md

For prompt rendering:
- .ai/skills/prompt-rendering.md

For sidecar/auth/context:
- .ai/skills/sidecar-auth-context.md

For MCP/tools:
- .ai/skills/mcp-tools.md

For YAML schema:
- .ai/skills/yaml-schema.md

For the runtime engine:
- .ai/skills/runtime-engine.md

Reusable role personas live in `.ai/roles/`; end-to-end task recipes live in
`.ai/workflows/`. Validate work with `make check` before finishing.
